    "headline": "Apple’s China Smartphone Push Raises Questions On Margins And Valuation",
    "summary": "Apple reports a 23% surge in China smartphone sales, outpacing a declining market. The company is expanding share by using e-commerce discounts and qualifying the base iPhone 17 for government subsidies. Apple is absorbing higher memory chip costs instead of raising prices, supporting its competitive position in the region. For investors tracking NasdaqGS:AAPL, this shift in China comes at a time when the stock is priced at $247.99 and has returned 14.1% over the past year and 110.1% over...",
